description.narrative: UNICEF continued its support to the GoT to develop a comprehensive social protection mechanisms and robust Social Work Workforce Development system to better meet the needs of the vulnerable children, including children affected by migration, in contact/conflict with the law, emergencies, repatriated and children with disabilities. To ensure realisation of the fundamental rights of the most excluded children, UNICEF supported over 1,250 children affected by migration to obtain birth certificates and access basic service. Human interest stories and media products were developed, disseminated and broadcasted to demonstrate changes in lives of children. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:20/01/2022
